article.headline: Valparaiso 35, Davidson 29, OT
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. -- Jake Riedel scored from 2 yards out in overtime and Anthony Curry intercepted a Davidson pass, his second pick of the game, on the Wildcats' possession as Valparaiso came from 18 points down for a 35-29 victory Saturday. Ross Wiemer had 170 yards on 22 carries and three touchdowns, including scoring runs of 49 and 17 yards in the fourth quarter, as the Crusaders (2-3, 1-1 Pioneer) rallied from a 21-3 second quarter deficit. Valpo led 29-21 with 1:47 remaining when Davidson's Kanny Mantuo ran 1 yard for his second touchdown of the game, and Ryan Alexander connected with Kirk Konert for the 2-point conversion to tie the game for the Wildcats (2-3, 1-2). Alexander completed 14 of 26 passes for 142 yards and one touchdown in the game. After Mantuo and Chad Barnes both ran 9 yards for first quarter touchdowns, Justin Williams extended the Davidson lead to 21-3 after rambling 32 yards to score on a screen pass from Alexander with 5:20 left in the second quarter. Riedel had 75 yards on 14 carries as Valpo gained 351 yards on the ground.
